subSubSection.paragraph:
Head (
Fig. 1
) mostly pale yellow. Face pale yellow, with brown V-shaped median spot, lateral and ventral margin brown, pale brown groove near ventral margin; parafacial pale yellow, with narrow brown median stripe on basal 1/2 and an elliptical brown ventroapical spot. Frons pale yellow at basal 2/3 and black at apical 1/3, wider than long slightly, trapeziform (anterior margin shorter than posterior margin), with pair of narrow brownish median stripes extending to vertex; ocellar triangle blackish gray, ocellar seta developed, longer than anterior fronto-orbital seta, anterior fronto-orbital seta longer than half length of posterior fronto-orbital seta; fronto-orbital seta each with 1 blackish brown basal spot fused to a narrow stripe. Gena about 1/5 height of eye. Occiput black, with grayish pruinosity. Antenna yellow, flagellomere 1 about 1.7 times longer than high; arista blackish brown, pubescent, with short setulae. Short-horizontal brown stripe spot present between eye and antenna. Proboscis pale brownish yellow except white at tip, with yellowish and blackish setulae; palpus yellow except pale brown at tip, with black setulae.

Abdomen (
Fig. 5
) blackish brown, but syntergosternite and epandrium yellow; tergites 2–6 with grayish white median spot on anterior margin, 4 pairs of grayish white spots and 4–5 pairs of setae on posterior margin. Male genitalia (
Figs. 6–10
): syntergosternite slender, circular with pair of ventral processes in anterior view. Surstylus consisting of 1 anterior process and 1 posteroapical process in lateral view; anterior process long with setae, digitiform, posterior process short, widening apically and truncated; hypandrium broad, H-shaped. Gonopod claviform and slender, slightly curved inwards in ventral view (curved slightly dorsally in lateral view), with 4 long setulae; phallus without apical concavity, with a curved sclerite at apex, vertical to phallus. Phallapodeme as long as 1/2 length of phallus.
